		<title>Chapter Forty-Eight</title>
		<link>http://lleelowe.com/corvus/chapter-forty-eight/</link>
		<comments>http://lleelowe.com/corvus/chapter-forty-eight/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Thu, 08 Jul 2010 18:46:54 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>llowe</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Corvus]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://lleelowe.com/?p=521</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Print PDF &#8216;You are here to become that Corvus,&#8217; the birdman says. Zach shrugs off his hood, the wind slicing through his jaggedly shorn hair as though determined to bareblade him. He misses Stella terribly; get real, she&#8217;d have told this creature with an earthy laugh. It&#8217;s easy to picture the flash of her scissors, [...]]]></description>
