		<title>Chapter Forty-Seven</title>
		<link>http://lleelowe.com/corvus/chapter-forty-seven/</link>
		<comments>http://lleelowe.com/corvus/chapter-forty-seven/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Thu, 01 Jul 2010 15:33:34 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>llowe</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Corvus]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://lleelowe.com/?p=519</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Print PDF At Stella&#8217;s name, Zach closed his eyes against and against, lashes trembling. He made no sound except the sound of a laboured bellows, as if he had to remind himself to breathe. Is there ever a right time for such news? His scar glinted with the veneer of healing, a pearly sheen, and [...]]]></description>
		<wfw:commentRss>http://lleelowe.com/corvus/chapter-forty-seven/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
