		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://lleelowe.com/?p=503</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Print PDF Pani has cleared overhanging snow from a section of the crevasse, shaved away its lip, and tamped down his harpoon as reinforcement, across the shaft of which he lowers a line that reaches Zach&#8217;s brow but looks too fragile to support his weight. To loop it round his chest is all but impossible. [...]]]></description>
		<wfw:commentRss>http://lleelowe.com/corvus/chapter-forty-two/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
